 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search PT Faculty- School of Fashion The New School 138 reviews New York, NY 10011 The New School 138 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Part-time Full Job Description Parsons School of Fashion at The New School University is seeking applications from academics, creative practitioners and industry professionals who would like to contribute to teaching on the following programs as part-time faculty members: 
 AAS Fashion Design AAS Fashion Marketing and Communication BFA Fashion Design MPS Fashion Management MFA Textiles 
 
In particular, we are looking for expertise in the following areas and the ability to apply skills and knowledge in the context of fashion, broadly considered: 
 Materiality and textile innovation Product design and wearable technology Systems thinking and human-centered design Digital communication and marketing Data analytics and artificial intelligence Business and entrepreneurship 
 
Part-time faculty are responsible for: developing course content and syllabi in consultation with Program Leadership; attending all classes they are assigned to teach as scheduled by the University; reporting any emergency faculty absences to the PTF Manager and/or Program Leadership; recording student attendance in a timely manner within two days of each class session; and adhering to all University policies (ie., FERPA, exclusive use of New School email, etc.), as outlined in the ACT-UAW Local 7902 Collective Bargaining Agreement. 
 
